This place was a nice little airport cafe. The staff was super nice, the breakfast burrito was solid (not authentic, but exactly what I wanted -- eggs and bacon wrapped in a tortilla with some salsa to dunk it in), and the coffee was good. They kept things moving quickly, and were just so friendly and welcoming that I felt all warm and fuzzy as I waited on my 3 hours delayed flight x_X

